    link(rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Montserrat:400,700|Raleway:400,700")
    link(rel='stylesheet' href='/css/ionicons.css')
    link(rel='stylesheet' href='/css/style.css')

  body.landing-page
    nav.navbar.navbar-transparent.navbar-fixed-top.navbar-color-on-scroll
      .container
        //- Brand and toggle get grouped for better mobile display
        .navbar-header
          button.navbar-toggle(type='button', data-toggle='collapse', data-target='#navigation-example')
            span.sr-only Toggle navigation
            span.icon-bar
            span.icon-bar
            span.icon-bar
          a(href='/')
            .logo-container
              .logo
                img(src='/img/logo.png', alt='Exnode Logo', rel='tooltip', title='<div class="small-tip"><b>Exnode</b> is a web app powered by <b>ExpressJs</b>, <b>NodeJs</b> and <b>Sweat</b></div>', data-placement='bottom', data-html='true')
              .brand  Exnode
        #navigation-example.collapse.navbar-collapse
          ul.nav.navbar-nav.navbar-right
            li
              a(href='/users', rel='tooltip',  title='<div class="small-tip">There are currently <b>12 Users</b> online</div>', data-placement='bottom', data-html='true') Users
            li
              a(href='/') About
            li
              a(href='/', rel='tooltip',  title='<div class="small-tip">Well, it looks like you are not SignedIn.</div>', data-placement='bottom', data-html='true') Login
            li
              a.btn.btn-simple.btn-white.btn-just-icon(href='#')
                i(class="icon ion-social-facebook")
            li
              a.btn.btn-simple.btn-white.btn-just-icon(href='#')
                i(class="icon ion-social-twitter")
            li
              a.btn.btn-simple.btn-white.btn-just-icon(href='#')
                i(class="icon ion-social-github")
    .wrapper 
      .header.header-filter
        .container
          .row
            .col-md-8.col-md-offset-2
              .brand
                h1 Expressing Node
                h3 A MEAN app built on Emotions, Tears, Sweat, Blood, Coffee and Sleepless Nights 
      .main.main-raised
        .container
          .section.text-center.section-landing
            .row
              .col-md-8.col-md-offset-2
                h2.title 
                  b What Exactly is Exnode?
                h5.description
                  | You are probably wondering, what is being Expressed. Just so you know, NodeJS is awesome and ExpressJS even makes it more awesome when backed by MongoDB. The fact this is a Hobby project even makes it more fun. Planning on integrating it with ReactJS later but I might fallback on AngularJS. Not because am all Mathematical, but just feeling a little M.E.A.N. About what is does, carry on!
            .features
              .row
                .col-md-4
                  .info
                    .icon
                      i.icon.ion-ios-color-filter-outline
                    h4.info-title Tightly Intergrated
                    p
                      | NPM ready. Just run `npm install --save exnode` and you will be up and running with a MEAN stacked app. Exnode is regularly updated with every update of its dependencies.
                .col-md-4
                  .info
                    .icon
                      i.icon.ion-ios-cog-outline
                    h4.info-title Beautifully Setup
                    p
                      |Designers and developers alike will really love Exnode. Based on Material Bootstrap by Creative Tim on the looks and Pure JS on the back, Exnode pleases the eye anytime.
                .col-md-4
                  .info
                    .icon
                      i.icon.ion-ios-compose-outline
                    h4.info-title Notetaking Rebooted
                    p
                      | For now, let's assume this is a Note taking ToDo app, because calling it Hello World is old fashioned. May be a Social Networking app later, but well, that for later.
      footer.footer
        .container
          nav.pull-left
            ul
              li
                a(href='/') Exnode
              li
                a(href='/') Contact
              li
                a(href='https://www.twitter.com/exnode') Tweet
